Patch summary:
Sign the EmulatedCamera provider APEX with the shared vendor HAL key so
apexd can activate a camera HAL at all.

The cuttlefish camera product config (device/google/cuttlefish
shared/camera/device_vendor.mk) unconditionally installs two multi-install
variants of the same APEX name:
- com.google.emulated.camera.provider.hal (this project, GoogleCamera HWL
  emulated cameras) signed with its own local key, and
- com.google.emulated.camera.provider.hal.v4l2 (device/google/cuttlefish
  guest/hals/virtio_media) signed with the shared vendor HAL key
  (hardware/interfaces/apexkey's com.android.hardware.key).

apexd requires every APEX participating in multi-install selection to be
signed with the same public key. Because the two variants differ, boot logs
show "Multi-install APEXes for com.google.emulated.camera.provider.hal have
different public keys." and apexd activates NEITHER variant: cameraserver
reports zero camera devices even though the bootconfig selector
(ro.boot.vendor.apex.com.google.emulated.camera.provider.hal) and the
emu_camera_*.json configs are all present. Confirmed on a live 2026-07-11
ika_arm64 instance; the built vendor/apex files carried different
apex_pubkey payloads. User-visible fallout: anything that opens a camera
dies -- e.g. Chromium's Cardboard VR QR-scanner activity crashes the
browser with "Unable to resume activity" and its window composites as
solid magenta.

Fix: sign this project's variants with the same shared vendor HAL key the
v4l2 variant already uses. This direction (rather than re-keying the v4l2
APEX) is required by Soong namespaces: EmulatedCamera is its own
soong_namespace, so its key modules are not visible from
device/google/cuttlefish, while the root-namespace com.android.hardware.key
is visible everywhere. The now-unreferenced local apex_key/certificate
modules are left in place to keep the diff minimal.

diff --git a/devices/EmulatedCamera/hwl/apex/Android.bp b/devices/EmulatedCamera/hwl/apex/Android.bp
index a2f754f..e6d16ff 100644
--- a/devices/EmulatedCamera/hwl/apex/Android.bp
+++ b/devices/EmulatedCamera/hwl/apex/Android.bp
@@ -43,8 +43,13 @@ prebuilt_etc {
 apex_defaults {
     name: "com.google.emulated.camera.provider.hal.defaults",
     manifest: "apex_manifest.json",
-    key: "com.google.emulated.camera.provider.hal.key",
-    certificate: ":com.google.emulated.camera.provider.hal.certificate",
+    // Multi-install APEX selection requires every variant of
+    // com.google.emulated.camera.provider.hal to be signed with the same key;
+    // the v4l2 variant (device/google/cuttlefish guest/hals/virtio_media) uses
+    // the shared vendor HAL key, so sign this one with it too or apexd
+    // activates neither and the guest boots with zero cameras.
+    key: "com.android.hardware.key",
+    certificate: ":com.android.hardware.certificate",
     file_contexts: "file_contexts",
     updatable: false,
     // Install the apex in /vendor/apex
